en_4844930_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – A five-judge bench has been appointed to consider the writ petition filed requesting an injunction order be issued against the death penalty.
en_4844930_1	The writ petition has been filed before the Court of Appeal by journalist Malinda Seneviratne.
en_4844930_2	The other members of the bench headed by President of the Court of Appeal Yasantha Kodagoda, are Justices Deepali Wijesundara, Janak De Silva, Achala Wengappuli and Arjuna Obeysekera.
en_4844930_3	News 1st correspondent noted that the writ petition is to be considered before the five-judge bench today(July 02).
